{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I have 18 minutes to tell you what happened"},{"time":2000,"text":"over the past six million years."},{"time":5000,"text":"All right."},{"time":7000,"text":"We all have come from a long way,"},{"time":10000,"text":"here in Africa, and converged in this region of Africa,"},{"time":13000,"text":"which is a place where 90 percent of our evolutionary process took place."},{"time":19000,"text":"And I say that not because I am African,"},{"time":22000,"text":"but it's in Africa that you find the earliest evidence"},{"time":25000,"text":"for human ancestors, upright walking traces,"},{"time":30000,"text":"even the first technologies in the form of stone tools."},{"time":33000,"text":"So we all are Africans, and welcome home."},{"time":36000,"text":"All right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"I'm a paleoanthropologist, and my job is to define"},{"time":41000,"text":"man's place in nature and explore what makes us human."},{"time":45000,"text":"And today, I will use Selam, the earliest child ever discovered,"},{"time":49000,"text":"to tell you a story of all of us."},{"time":51000,"text":"Selam is our most complete skeleton of a three-year-old girl"},{"time":55000,"text":"who lived and died 3.3 million years ago."},{"time":59000,"text":"She belongs to the species known as Australopithecus afarensis."},{"time":63000,"text":"You don't need to remember that."},{"time":65000,"text":"That's the Lucy species, and was found by my research team"},{"time":69000,"text":"in December of 2000 in an area called Dikika."},{"time":72000,"text":"It's in the northeastern part of Ethiopia."},{"time":74000,"text":"And Selam means peace in many Ethiopian languages."},{"time":77000,"text":"We use that name to celebrate peace in the region and in the planet."},{"time":83000,"text":"And the fact that it was the cover story of all these famous magazines"},{"time":87000,"text":"gives you already an idea of her significance, I think."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90000,"text":"After I was invited by TED, I did some digging,"},{"time":93000,"text":"because that's what we do, to know about my host."},{"time":96000,"text":"You don't just jump into an invitation."},{"time":98000,"text":"And I learned that the first technology appeared"},{"time":100000,"text":"in the form of stone tools, 2.6 million years ago."},{"time":103000,"text":"First entertainment comes evidence from flutes that are 35,000 years old."},{"time":108000,"text":"And evidence for first design comes 75,000 years old -- beads."},{"time":114000,"text":"And you can do the same with your genes and track them back in time."},{"time":119000,"text":"And DNA analysis of living humans and chimpanzees"},{"time":123000,"text":"teaches us today that we diverged sometime around seven million years ago"},{"time":127000,"text":"and that these two species share over 98 percent of the same genetic material."},{"time":133000,"text":"I think knowing this is a very useful context"},{"time":135000,"text":"within which we can think of our ancestry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"However, DNA analysis informs us only about"},{"time":143000,"text":"the beginning and the end, telling us nothing"},{"time":147000,"text":"about what happened in the middle."},{"time":149000,"text":"So, for us, paleoanthropologists, our job is to find the hard evidence,"},{"time":154000,"text":"the fossil evidence, to fill in this gap"},{"time":157000,"text":"and see the different stages of development."},{"time":160000,"text":"Because it's only when you do that, that you can talk about --"},{"time":163000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":167000,"text":"it's only when you do that, [that] you can talk about"},{"time":170000,"text":"how we looked like and how we behaved at different times,"},{"time":174000,"text":"and how those likes and looks and behaviors changed through time."},{"time":179000,"text":"That then gives you an access"},{"time":181000,"text":"to explore the biological mechanisms"},{"time":184000,"text":"and forces that are responsible for this gradual change"},{"time":187000,"text":"that made us what we are today."},{"time":190000,"text":"But finding the hard evidence is a very complicated endeavor."},{"time":194000,"text":"It's a systematic and scientific approach,"},{"time":197000,"text":"which takes you to places that are remote, hot, hostile and often with no access."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203000,"text":"Just to give you an example, when I went to Dikika,"},{"time":205000,"text":"where Selam was found, in '99 -- and it's about 500 kilometers"},{"time":209000,"text":"from Addis Ababa, the capital of Ethiopia."},{"time":213000,"text":"It took us only seven hours to do the first 470 kilometers of the 500,"},{"time":220000,"text":"but took four, solid hours to do the last only 30 kilometers."},{"time":225000,"text":"With the help of the locals and using just shovels and picks, I made my way."},{"time":229000,"text":"I was the first person to actually drive a car to the spot."},{"time":233000,"text":"When you get there, this is what you see,"},{"time":236000,"text":"and it's the vastness of the place which makes you feel helpless and vulnerable."},{"time":241000,"text":"And once you make it there, the big question is where to start."},{"time":245000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":247000,"text":"And you find nothing for years and years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250000,"text":"When I go to places like this, which are paleontological sites,"},{"time":254000,"text":"it's like going to a game park, an extinct game park."},{"time":258000,"text":"But what you find are not the human remains,"},{"time":261000,"text":"such as Selam and Lucy, on a day-to-day basis."},{"time":264000,"text":"You find elephants, rhinos, monkeys, pigs, etc."},{"time":268000,"text":"But you could ask, how could these large mammals"},{"time":270000,"text":"live in this desert environment?"},{"time":272000,"text":"Of course, they cannot, but I'm telling you already"},{"time":274000,"text":"that the environment and the carrying capacity"},{"time":277000,"text":"of this region was drastically different from what we have today."},{"time":282000,"text":"A very important environmental lesson could be learned from this."},{"time":286000,"text":"Anyway, once we made it there, then it's a game park, as I said, an extinct game park."},{"time":292000,"text":"And our ancestors lived in that game park,"},{"time":295000,"text":"but were just the minorities. They were not as successful"},{"time":297000,"text":"and as widespread as the Homo sapiens that we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302000,"text":"To tell you just an example, an anecdote about their rarity,"},{"time":305000,"text":"I was going to this place every year and would do fieldwork here,"},{"time":310000,"text":"and the assistants, of course, helped me do the surveys."},{"time":313000,"text":"They would find a bone and tell me, \"Here is what you're looking for.\""},{"time":315000,"text":"I would say, \"No, that's an elephant.\""},{"time":316000,"text":"Again, another one, \"That's a monkey.\" \"That's a pig,\" etc."},{"time":319000,"text":"So one of my assistants, who never went to school, said to me, \"Listen, Zeray."},{"time":322000,"text":"You either don't know what you're looking for,"},{"time":324000,"text":"or you're looking in the wrong place,\" he said."},{"time":327000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":328000,"text":"And I said, \"Why?\" \"Because there were elephants and lions,"},{"time":331000,"text":"and the people were scared and went somewhere else."},{"time":333000,"text":"Let's go somewhere else.\""},{"time":335000,"text":"Well, he was very tired, and it's really tiring."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337000,"text":"It was then, after such hard work and many frustrating years that we found Selam,"},{"time":342000,"text":"and you see the face here covered by sandstone."},{"time":345000,"text":"And here is actually the spinal column"},{"time":347000,"text":"and the whole torso encased in a sandstone block,"},{"time":351000,"text":"because she was buried by a river."},{"time":354000,"text":"What you have here seems to be nothing,"},{"time":356000,"text":"but contains an incredible amount of scientific information"},{"time":360000,"text":"that helps us explore what makes us human."},{"time":363000,"text":"This is the earliest and most complete juvenile human ancestor"},{"time":367000,"text":"ever found in the history of paleoanthropology,"},{"time":369000,"text":"an amazing piece of our long, long history."},{"time":373000,"text":"There were these three people and me, and I am taking the pictures,"},{"time":376000,"text":"that's why I am not in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378000,"text":"How would you feel if you were me? You have something extraordinary in your hand,"},{"time":381000,"text":"but you are in the middle of nowhere?"},{"time":383000,"text":"The feeling I had was a deep and quiet happiness and excitement,"},{"time":388000,"text":"of course accompanied by a huge sense of responsibility,"},{"time":391000,"text":"of making sure everything is safe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394000,"text":"Here is a close-up of the fossil, after five years of cleaning,"},{"time":399000,"text":"preparation and description, which was very long,"},{"time":403000,"text":"as I had to expose the bones from the sandstone block"},{"time":406000,"text":"I just showed you in the previous slide."},{"time":408000,"text":"It took five years."},{"time":409000,"text":"In a way, this was like the second birth for the child, after 3.3 million years,"},{"time":414000,"text":"but the labor was very long."},{"time":417000,"text":"And here is full scale -- it's a tiny bone."},{"time":421000,"text":"And in the middle is the minister of Ethiopian tourism,"},{"time":424000,"text":"who came to visit the National Museum of Ethiopia while I was working there."},{"time":428000,"text":"And you see me worried and trying to protect my child,"},{"time":431000,"text":"because you don't leave anyone with this kind of child,"},{"time":434000,"text":"even a minister."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437000,"text":"So then, once you've done that, the next stage is to know what it is."},{"time":441000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":444000,"text":"Once that was done, then it was possible to compare."},{"time":448000,"text":"We were able to tell that she belonged"},{"time":450000,"text":"to the human family tree because the legs, the foot,"},{"time":454000,"text":"and some features clearly showed that she walked upright,"},{"time":458000,"text":"and upright walking is a hallmark in humanity."},{"time":461000,"text":"But in addition, if you compare the skull"},{"time":464000,"text":"with a comparably aged chimpanzee and little George Bush here,"},{"time":467000,"text":"you see that you have vertical forehead."},{"time":471000,"text":"And you see that in humans, because of the development"},{"time":474000,"text":"of the pre-frontal cortex, it's called."},{"time":476000,"text":"You don't see that in chimpanzees,"},{"time":479000,"text":"and you don't see this very projecting canine."},{"time":483000,"text":"So she belongs to our family tree, but within that, of course,"},{"time":486000,"text":"you do detailed analysis, and we know now"},{"time":488000,"text":"that she belongs to the Lucy species,"},{"time":490000,"text":"known as Australopithecus afarensis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493000,"text":"The next exciting question is, girl or boy?"},{"time":496000,"text":"And how old was she when she died?"},{"time":498000,"text":"You can determine the sex of the individual"},{"time":501000,"text":"based on the size of the teeth."},{"time":504000,"text":"How?"},{"time":505000,"text":"You know, in primates, there is this phenomenon"},{"time":507000,"text":"called sexual dimorphism, which simply means"},{"time":509000,"text":"males are larger than females and males have larger teeth"},{"time":511000,"text":"than the females."},{"time":513000,"text":"But to do that, you need the permanent dentition,"},{"time":515000,"text":"which you don't see here, because what you have here"},{"time":517000,"text":"are the baby teeth."},{"time":519000,"text":"But using the CT scanning technology,"},{"time":521000,"text":"which is normally used for medical purposes,"},{"time":523000,"text":"you can go deep into the mouth and come up with this beautiful image"},{"time":526000,"text":"showing you both the baby teeth here"},{"time":528000,"text":"and the still-growing adult teeth here."},{"time":532000,"text":"So when you measure those teeth,"},{"time":534000,"text":"it was clear that she turned out to be a girl"},{"time":537000,"text":"with very small canine teeth."},{"time":540000,"text":"And to know how old she was when she died, what you do is"},{"time":542000,"text":"you do an informed estimate, and you say, how much time would be required"},{"time":548000,"text":"to form this amount of teeth, and the answer was three."},{"time":553000,"text":"So, this girl died when she was about three,"},{"time":556000,"text":"3.3 million years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558000,"text":"So, with all that information, the big question is --"},{"time":561000,"text":"what do we actually -- what does she tell us?"},{"time":565000,"text":"To answer this question, we can phrase another question."},{"time":567000,"text":"What do we actually know about our ancestors?"},{"time":570000,"text":"We want to know how they looked like, how they behaved,"},{"time":572000,"text":"how they walked around,"},{"time":574000,"text":"and how they lived and grew up."},{"time":577000,"text":"And among the answers that you can get from this skeleton"},{"time":582000,"text":"are included: first, this skeleton documents,"},{"time":587000,"text":"for the first time, how infants looked over three million years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592000,"text":"And second, she tells us that she walked upright,"},{"time":595000,"text":"but had some adaptation for tree climbing."},{"time":598000,"text":"And more interesting, however,"},{"time":600000,"text":"is the brain in this child was still growing."},{"time":602000,"text":"At age three, if you have a still-growing brain,"},{"time":605000,"text":"it's a human behavior."},{"time":607000,"text":"In chimps, by age three, the brain is formed over 90 percent."},{"time":612000,"text":"That's why they can cope with their environment"},{"time":615000,"text":"very easily after birth -- faster than us, anyway."},{"time":618000,"text":"But in humans, we continue to grow our brains."},{"time":620000,"text":"That's why we need care from our parents."},{"time":623000,"text":"But that care means also you learn."},{"time":625000,"text":"You spend more time with your parents."},{"time":627000,"text":"And that's very characteristic of humans and it's called childhood,"},{"time":630000,"text":"which is this extended dependence of human children"},{"time":633000,"text":"on their family or parents."},{"time":636000,"text":"So, the still-growing brain in this individual"},{"time":640000,"text":"tells us that childhood, which requires"},{"time":643000,"text":"an incredible social organization,"},{"time":646000,"text":"a very complex social organization,"},{"time":648000,"text":"emerged over three million years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650000,"text":"So, by being at the cusp of our evolutionary history,"},{"time":654000,"text":"Selam unites us all and gives us a unique account"},{"time":659000,"text":"on what makes us human."},{"time":662000,"text":"But not everything was human, and I will give you"},{"time":665000,"text":"a very exciting example."},{"time":667000,"text":"This is called the hyoid bone. It's a bone which is right here."},{"time":669000,"text":"It supports your tongue from behind."},{"time":671000,"text":"It's, in a way, your voice box."},{"time":674000,"text":"It determines the type of voice you produce."},{"time":678000,"text":"It was not known in the fossil record,"},{"time":680000,"text":"and we have it in this skeleton."},{"time":683000,"text":"When we did the analysis of this bone, it was clear"},{"time":687000,"text":"that it looked very chimp-like, chimpanzee-like."},{"time":691000,"text":"So if you were there 3.3 million years ago,"},{"time":695000,"text":"to hear when this girl was crying out for her mother,"},{"time":698000,"text":"she would have sounded more like a chimpanzee than a human."},{"time":701000,"text":"Maybe you're wondering, \"So, you see this ape feature, human feature, ape feature."},{"time":705000,"text":"What does that tell us?\""},{"time":707000,"text":"You know, that is very exciting for us,"},{"time":709000,"text":"because it demonstrates that things were changing slowly and progressively,"},{"time":712000,"text":"and that evolution is in the making."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715000,"text":"To summarize the significance of this fossil,"},{"time":718000,"text":"we can say the following."},{"time":720000,"text":"Up to now, the knowledge that we had about our ancestors"},{"time":724000,"text":"came essentially from adult individuals"},{"time":728000,"text":"because the fossils, the baby fossils, were missing."},{"time":731000,"text":"They don't preserve well, as you know."},{"time":733000,"text":"So the knowledge that we had about our ancestors,"},{"time":737000,"text":"on how they looked like, how they behaved,"},{"time":739000,"text":"was kind of biased toward adults."},{"time":744000,"text":"Imagine somebody coming from Mars"},{"time":747000,"text":"and his job is to report on the type of people"},{"time":749000,"text":"occupying our planet Earth, and you hide all the babies,"},{"time":752000,"text":"the children, and he goes back and reports."},{"time":756000,"text":"Can you imagine how much biased his report would be?"},{"time":760000,"text":"That's what somehow we were doing so far"},{"time":762000,"text":"in the absence of the fossil children,"},{"time":764000,"text":"so I think the new fossil fixes this problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"So, I think the most important question at the end is,"},{"time":774000,"text":"what do we actually learn from specimens like this"},{"time":777000,"text":"and from our past in general?"},{"time":780000,"text":"Of course, in addition to extracting this huge amount"},{"time":783000,"text":"of scientific information as to what makes us human,"},{"time":786000,"text":"you know, the many human ancestors that have existed"},{"time":789000,"text":"over the past six million years -- and there are more than 10 --"},{"time":793000,"text":"they did not have the knowledge, the technology and sophistications"},{"time":796000,"text":"that we, Homo sapiens, have today."},{"time":798000,"text":"But if this species, ancient species,"},{"time":802000,"text":"would travel in time and see us today,"},{"time":805000,"text":"they would very much be very proud of their legacy,"},{"time":810000,"text":"because they became the ancestors of"},{"time":812000,"text":"the most successful species in the universe."},{"time":814000,"text":"And they were probably not aware of this future legacy,"},{"time":816000,"text":"but they did great."},{"time":818000,"text":"Now the question is, we Homo sapiens today"},{"time":821000,"text":"are in a position to decide about the future of our planet, possibly more."},{"time":827000,"text":"So the question is, are we up to the challenge?"},{"time":830000,"text":"And can we really do better than these primitive,"},{"time":833000,"text":"small-brained ancestors?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":836000,"text":"Among the most pressing challenges that our species"},{"time":840000,"text":"is faced with today are the chronic problems of Africa."},{"time":845000,"text":"Needless to list them here, and there are more competent people"},{"time":848000,"text":"to talk about this."},{"time":851000,"text":"Still, in my opinion, we have two choices."},{"time":857000,"text":"One is to continue to see a poor, ill, crying Africa,"},{"time":863000,"text":"carrying guns, that depends on other people forever,"},{"time":868000,"text":"or to promote an Africa which is confident,"},{"time":873000,"text":"peaceful, independent, but cognizant of its huge problems"},{"time":877000,"text":"and great values at the same time."},{"time":881000,"text":"I am for the second option, and I'm sure many of you are."},{"time":886000,"text":"And the key is to promote a positive African attitude towards Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":896000,"text":"That's because we Africans concentrate --"},{"time":900000,"text":"I am from Ethiopia, by the way --"},{"time":902000,"text":"we concentrate too much on how we are seen"},{"time":904000,"text":"from elsewhere, or from outside."},{"time":907000,"text":"I think it's important to promote in a more positive way"},{"time":912000,"text":"on how we see ourselves."},{"time":915000,"text":"That's what I call positive African attitude."},{"time":918000,"text":"So finally, I would like to say,"},{"time":921000,"text":"so let's help Africa walk upright and forward,"},{"time":926000,"text":"then we all can be proud of our future legacy as a species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}